---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../utils/i18n';

const locale = 'en';
const t = useTranslations(locale);
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ - Ionyx Framework" description="Frequently asked questions about Ionyx">
	<section class="py-20 hero-gradient">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
				<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
					Frequently Asked <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue bg-clip-text text-transparent">Questions</span>
				</h1>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
					Everything you need to know about Ionyx
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="py-20">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<!-- Framework Comparison -->
					<div class="glass-dark rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
						<button class="w-full p-6 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('expanded')">
							<div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
								<div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
									<span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">F</span>
								</div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What's the difference from other frameworks?</h3>
							</div>
							<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
							</svg>
						</button>
						<div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
							<p class="mb-4">
								<strong class="text-white">Ionyx is designed for minimalist desktop application development.</strong> 
								Electron, Tauri™, and other frameworks are great options, but Ionyx offers a different approach:
							</p>
							<div class="bg-dark-tertiary rounded-lg p-4 border border-dark-border mb-4">
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">🎯 <strong class="text-white">Electron:</strong> Full-featured, Node.js based</p>
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">🎯 <strong class="text-white">Tauri™:</strong> Rust based, extensive ecosystem</p>
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">🎯 <strong class="text-white">Ionyx:</strong> Minimalist, ultra-small binary</p>
							</div>
							<p class="mb-4">
								Ionyx focuses only on the most essential features, targeting sub-3MB runtime. 
								This makes it ideal for small and fast applications.
							</p>
							<p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
								TAURI is a trademark of The Tauri Programme within the Commons Conservancy.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- Binary Size -->
					<div class="glass-dark rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
						<button class="w-full p-6 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('expanded')">
							<div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
								<div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
									<span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">B</span>
								</div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">How is the 1.66MB binary size possible?</h3>
							</div>
							<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
							</svg>
						</button>
						<div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
							<p class="mb-4">
								Thanks to minimalist engineering principles:
							</p>
							<ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>No unnecessary dependencies</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Only the most essential WRY (0.54.2) and TAO (0.34.5) libraries</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>No extra runtime (uses system WebView)</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Optimized Rust code</span>
								</li>
							</ul>
							<div class="bg-dark-tertiary rounded-lg p-4 border border-dark-border">
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
									<strong class="text-white">Breakdown:</strong> WRY (0.54.2) + TAO (0.34.5) + Ionyx Core (~0.8MB) = 1.66MB
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- Frontend Framework -->
					<div class="glass-dark rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
						<button class="w-full p-6 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('expanded')">
							<div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
								<div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
									<span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">F</span>
								</div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Which frontend frameworks does it support?</h3>
							</div>
							<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
							</svg>
						</button>
						<div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
							<p class="mb-4">
								<strong class="text-white">Ionyx is frontend-agnostic.</strong> 
								It works with any frontend framework:
							</p>
							<ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>React + TypeScript</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Vue.js + TypeScript</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Svelte + TypeScript</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Vanilla JavaScript</span>
								</li>
							</ul>
							<div class="bg-dark-tertiary rounded-lg p-4 border border-dark-border">
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
									<strong class="text-white">Note:</strong> Ionyx only provides the backend, frontend is entirely yours.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- Performance -->
					<div class="glass-dark rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
						<button class="w-full p-6 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('expanded')">
							<div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
								<div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
									<span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">P</span>
								</div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What are the performance advantages?</h3>
							</div>
							<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
							</svg>
						</button>
						<div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
							<p class="mb-4">
								<strong class="text-white">Ionyx's performance advantages:</strong>
							</p>
							<ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>&lt;30ms application startup time</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>10-20MB memory usage</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Minimal CPU usage</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>System WebView for native performance</span>
								</li>
							</ul>
							<div class="bg-dark-tertiary rounded-lg p-4 border border-dark-border">
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
									<strong class="text-white">Comparison:</strong> Electron (100-200MB) vs Ionyx (10-20MB)
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- Production Ready -->
					<div class="glass-dark rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
						<button class="w-full p-6 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('expanded')">
							<div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
								<div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
									<span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">P</span>
								</div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">Is it production ready?</h3>
							</div>
							<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
							</svg>
						</button>
						<div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
							<p class="mb-4">
								<strong class="text-white">Ionyx is currently in development.</strong>
							</p>
							<ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-yellow-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Core APIs are being developed</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-yellow-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>CLI tools are being worked on</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-yellow-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Documentation is being expanded</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Open to community contributions</span>
								</li>
							</ul>
							<div class="bg-dark-tertiary rounded-lg p-4 border border-dark-border">
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
									<strong class="text-white">Status:</strong> Alpha version, not ready for production
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- Learning Curve -->
					<div class="glass-dark rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
						<button class="w-full p-6 text-left flex items-center justify-between hover:bg-white/5 transition-colors" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('expanded')">
							<div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
								<div class="w-8 h-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-ionyx-neon-purple to-ionyx-neon-blue rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
									<span class="text-white font-bold text-sm">L</span>
								</div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">How is the learning curve?</h3>
							</div>
							<svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
							</svg>
						</button>
						<div class="px-6 pb-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
							<p class="mb-4">
								<strong class="text-white">Ionyx is easy to learn:</strong>
							</p>
							<ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Simple CLI commands</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Standard web technologies</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Few concepts to learn</span>
								</li>
								<li class="flex items-start">
									<span class="text-green-400 mr-2">•</span>
									<span>Comprehensive documentation</span>
								</li>
							</ul>
							<div class="bg-dark-tertiary rounded-lg p-4 border border-dark-border">
								<p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
									<strong class="text-white">Requirements:</strong> HTML/CSS/JS and basic Rust knowledge is sufficient
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- CTA Section -->
				<div class="mt-16 text-center">
					<div class="glass p-8 rounded-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto">
						<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
							Have more questions?
						</h2>
						<p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">
							Join our community or discuss on GitHub.
						</p>
						<div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center space-y-4 sm:space-y-0 sm:space-x-4">
							<a href="https://github.com/ionyx-apps/ionyx/discussions" class="btn-primary w-full sm:w-auto">
								GitHub Discussions
							</a>
							<a href="https://discord.gg/ionyx" class="btn-secondary w-full sm:w-auto">
								Discord
							</a>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.glass-dark.expanded .px-6.pb-6 {
		display: block;
	}
	
	.glass-dark:not(.expanded) .px-6.pb-6 {
		display: none;
	}
</style>
